tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose metabolism or possible prediabetes. Creatinine is slightly above normal, which may suggest reduced renal function and warrants monitoring. All other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend follow-up for glycemic control and renal function assessment.
